{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Specialize the behavior of the system language model by using a custom adapter you train."}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"Foundation Models"}],"images":[{"type":"card","identifier":"loading-and-using-a-custom-adapter-with-foundation-models-PageImage-card.png"}],"title":"Loading and using a custom adapter with Foundation Models","role":"article"},"identifier":{"url":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/loading-and-using-a-custom-adapter-with-foundation-models","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["/documentation/foundationmodels/loading-and-using-a-custom-adapter-with-foundation-models"]}],"sections":[],"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Loading the model with an adapter","anchor":"Loading-the-model-with-an-adapter","identifiers":["doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/BundleResources/Entitlements/com.apple.developer.foundation-model-adapter","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/init(adapter:guardrails:)","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/Adapter"],"generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use an adapter to adapt the on-device foundation model to fit your specific"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use case without needing to retrain the entire model from scratch. Before you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can load a custom adapter, you first need to train one with an adapter training"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"toolkit. The toolkit uses Python and Pytorch, and requires familiarity with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"training machine-learning models. After you train an adapter, you can use the toolkit"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to export a package in the format that Xcode and the Foundation Models framework"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"expects."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you train an adapter you need to make it available for deployment into your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"app. An adapter file is large — 160 MB or more — so don’t bundle them in your","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"app. Instead, use App Store Connect, or host the asset on your server, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"download the correct adapter for a person’s device on-demand."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each adapter is compatible with a "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"single specific"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" system model"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"version. You must train a new adapter for every new base model version. A runtime"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"error occurs if your app runs on a person’s device without a compatible adapter.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Important","style":"important"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For more information about the adapter training toolkit, see "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https://developer.apple.com/apple-intelligence/foundation-models-adapter/","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For more information about asset packs, see ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/BackgroundAssets","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Test-a-local-adapter-in-Xcode","level":2,"text":"Test a local adapter in Xcode","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After you train an adapter with the adapter training toolkit, store your "},{"code":".fmadapter","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":""},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"package files in a different directory from your app. Then, open "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".fmadapter"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"packages with Xcode to locally preview each adapter’s metadata and version"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"compatibility before you deploy the adapter.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you train multiple adapters:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Find the adapter package that’s compatible with the macOS version of the Mac on which you run Xcode."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Select the compatible adapter file in Finder.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Copy its full file path to the clipboard by pressing Option + Command + C.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Initialize "},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/Adapter","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" with the file path.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["// The absolute path to your adapter.","let localURL = URL(filePath: \"absolute/path/to/my_adapter.fmadapter\")","","// Initialize the adapter by using the local URL.","let adapter = try SystemLanguageModel.Adapter(fileURL: localURL)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"After you initialize an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Adapter"},{"type":"text","text":", create an instance of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with it:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["// An instance of the the system language model using your adapter.","let customAdapterModel = SystemLanguageModel(adapter: adapter)","","// Create a session and prompt the model.","let session = LanguageModelSession(model: customAdapterModel)","let response = try await session.respond(to: \"Your prompt here\")"],"syntax":"swift"},{"style":"important","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Only import adapter files into your Xcode project for local testing,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"then remove them before you publish your app. Adapter files are large, so download","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"them on-demand by using "},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/BackgroundAssets","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Important"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Testing adapters requires a physical device and isn’t supported on Simulator."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"When you’re ready to deploy adapters in your app, you need the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/BundleResources/Entitlements/com.apple.developer.foundation-model-adapter","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"entitlement. You don’t need this entitlement to train or locally test adapters."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"To request access to use the entitlement, log in to Apple Developer and see"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https://developer.apple.com/contact/request/foundation-models-framework-adapter-entitlement"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"text":"Bundle adapters as asset packs","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Bundle-adapters-as-asset-packs"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When people use your app they only need the specific adapter that’s compatible","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with their device. Host your adapter assets on a server and use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/BackgroundAssets","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to manage downloads. For hosting, you can use your own server or have Apple","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"host your adapter assets. For more information about Apple-hosted asset packs, see ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https://developer.apple.com/help/app-store-connect/manage-asset-packs/overview-of-apple-hosted-asset-packs/"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/BackgroundAssets"},{"text":" framework has","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a type of asset pack specific to adapters that you create for the Foundation Models","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"framework. The Foundation Models adapter training toolkit helps you bundle your","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"adapters in the correct asset pack format. The toolkit uses the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ba-package"},{"type":"text","text":" command"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"line tool that’s included with Xcode 16 or later. If you train your adapters on a Linux GPU","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"machine, see "},{"identifier":"https://developer.apple.com/apple-intelligence/foundation-models-adapter/#how-to-train-adapters","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to set up a Python environment on your Mac. The adapter toolkit includes example","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"code that shows how to create the asset pack in the correct format.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After you generate an asset pack for each adapter, upload the asset packs to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"your server. For more information about uploading Apple-hosted adapters, see "},{"identifier":"https://developer.apple.com/help/app-store-connect/manage-asset-packs/upload-apple-hosted-asset-packs","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"text":"Configure an asset-download target in Xcode","level":2,"anchor":"Configure-an-asset-download-target-in-Xcode","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To download adapters at runtime, you need to add an asset-downloader extension target"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to your Xcode project:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Xcode, choose File > New > Target."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Choose the Background Download template under the Application Extension section.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Click next."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Enter a descriptive name, like “AssetDownloader”, for the product name.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Select the type of extension.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Click Finish.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The type of extension depends on whether you self-host them or Apple hosts them:"}]},{"items":[{"term":{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple-Hosted, Managed"}]},"definition":{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple hosts your adapter assets."}]}]}},{"term":{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Self-Hosted, Managed"}]},"definition":{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You use your server and make each device’s operating system automatically handle the download life cycle.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}},{"term":{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Self-Hosted, Unmanaged"}]},"definition":{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You use your server and manage the download life cycle."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}}],"type":"termList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After you create an asset-downloader extension target, check that your app target’s"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"info property list contains the required fields specific to your extension type:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"termList","items":[{"definition":{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},"term":{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple-Hosted, Managed"}]}}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"BAHasManagedAssetPacks"},{"text":" = YES","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"BAAppGroupID","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" = The string ID of the app group that your app and downloader extension"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"targets share."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"BAUsesAppleHosting"},{"type":"text","text":" = YES"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"items":[{"term":{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Self-Hosted, Managed","type":"text"}]},"definition":{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""}],"type":"paragraph"}]}}],"type":"termList"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"BAHasManagedAssetPacks","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" = YES"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"BAAppGroupID","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" = The string ID of the app group that your app and downloader extension","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"targets share.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you use "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Self-Hosted, Unmanaged"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", then you don’t need additional keys. For more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"information about configuring background assets with an extension, see "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/BackgroundAssets/configuring-an-unmanaged-background-assets-project","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Choose a compatible adapter at runtime","anchor":"Choose-a-compatible-adapter-at-runtime"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you create an asset-downloader extension, Xcode generates a Swift file —"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"BackgroundDownloadHandler.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" — that "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/BackgroundAssets","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"uses to download your adapters. Open the Swift file in Xcode and fill in the code"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"based on your target type. For "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple-Hosted, Managed","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Self-Hosted, Managed"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"extension types, complete the function "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"shouldDownload"},{"text":" with the following","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"code that chooses an adapter asset compatible with the runtime device:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["func shouldDownload(_ assetPack: AssetPack) -> Bool {","    // Check for any non-adapter assets your app has, like shaders. Remove the","    // check if your app doesn't have any non-adapter assets.","    if assetPack.id.hasPrefix(\"mygameshader\") {","        // Return false to filter out asset packs, or true to allow download.","        return true","    }","","    // Use the Foundation Models framework to check adapter compatibility with the runtime device.","    return SystemLanguageModel.Adapter.isCompatible(assetPack)","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If your extension type is ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Self-Hosted, Unmanaged","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", the file Xcode generates has"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"many functions in it for manual control over the download life cycle of your assets."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Load adapter assets in your app","anchor":"Load-adapter-assets-in-your-app"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After you configure an asset-downloader extension, you can start loading adapters."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Before you download an adapter, remove any outdated adapters that might be on a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"person’s device:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["SystemLanguageModel.Adapter.removeObsoleteAdapters()"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Create an instance of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/Adapter","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" using your adapter’s base name,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"but exclude the file extension. If a person’s device doesn’t have a compatible","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"adapter downloaded, your asset-downloader extension starts downloading a compatible"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"adapter asset pack:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let adapter = try SystemLanguageModel.Adapter(name: \"myAdapter\")"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Initializing a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/Adapter","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" starts a download automatically"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"when a person launches your app for the first time or their device needs an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"updated adapter. Because adapters can have a large data size they can take some"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time to download, especially if a person is on Wi-Fi or a cell network. If a person"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"doesn’t have a network connection, they aren’t able to use your adapter right away."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This method shows how to track the download status of an adapter:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["func checkAdapterDownload(name: String) async -> Bool {","    // Get the ID of the compatible adapter.","    let assetpackIDList = SystemLanguageModel.Adapter.compatibleAdapterIdentifiers(","        name: name","    )","","    if let assetPackID = assetpackIDList.first {","        // Get the download status asynchronous sequence.","        let statusUpdates = AssetPackManager.shared.statusUpdates(forAssetPackWithID: assetPackID)","","        // Use the current status to update any loading UI.","        for await status in statusUpdates {","            switch status {","            case .began(let assetPack):","                // The download started.","            case .paused(let assetPack):","                // The download is in a paused state.","            case .downloading(let assetPack, let progress):","                // The download in progress.","            case .finished(let assetPack):","                // The download is complete and the adapter is ready to use.","                return true","            case .failed(let assetPack, let error):","                // The download failed.","                return false","            @unknown default:","                // The download encountered an unknown status.","                fatalError()","            }","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For more details on tracking downloads for general assets, see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/BackgroundAssets/downloading-apple-hosted-asset-packs","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Before you attempt to use the adapter, you need to wait for the status to be in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/BackgroundAssets/AssetPackManager/DownloadStatusUpdate/finished(_:)","isActive":true},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"state. The system returns"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/BackgroundAssets/AssetPackManager/DownloadStatusUpdate/finished(_:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":""},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"immediately if no download is necessary.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["// Load the adapter.","let adapter = try SystemLanguageModel.Adapter(name: \"myAdapter\")","","// Wait for download to complete.","if await checkAdapterDownload(name: \"myAdapter\") {","    // Adapt the base model with your adapter.","    let adaptedModel = SystemLanguageModel(adapter: adapter)","    ","    // Start a session with the adapted model.","    let session = LanguageModelSession(model: adaptedModel)","    ","    // Start prompting the adapted model.","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Compile-your-draft-model","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Compile your draft model"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A draft model is an optional step when training your adapter that can speed up"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"inference. If your adapter includes a draft model, you can compile it for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"faster inference:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["// Load the adapter.","let adapter = try SystemLanguageModel.Adapter(name: \"myAdapter\")","","// Wait for download to complete.","if await checkAdapterDownload(name: \"myAdapter\") {","    do {","        // You can use your adapter without compiling the draft model, or during","        // compilation, but running inference with your adapter might be slower.","        try await adapter.compile()","    } catch let error {","        // Handle the draft model compilation error.","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For more about training draft models, see the “Optionally train the draft model”"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"section in "},{"identifier":"https://developer.apple.com/apple-intelligence/foundation-models-adapter/","overridingTitle":"Get started with Foundation Models adapter training","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get started with Foundation Models adapter training"}],"isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Compiling a draft model is a computationally expensive step, so use the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/BackgroundTasks","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" framework to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"configure a background task for your app. In your background task, call "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/Adapter/compile()","isActive":true},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"on your adapter to start compilation. For more information about using background","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"tasks, see ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/UIKit/using-background-tasks-to-update-your-app","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Compilation doesn’t run every time a person uses your app:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The first time a device downloads a new version of your adapter, a call to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/Adapter/compile()","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" fully compiles your draft model and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"saves it to the device.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"During subsequent launches of your app, a call to ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/Adapter/compile()"},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"checks for a saved compiled draft model and returns it immediately if it exists."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"name":"Important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Rate limiting protects device resources that are shared between all"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"apps and processes. If the framework determines that a new compilation is necessary,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"it rate-limits the compilation process on all platforms, excluding macOS, to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"three draft model compilations per-app, per-day."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"important","type":"aside"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The full compilation process runs every time you launch your app through Xcode"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"because Xcode assigns your app a new UUID for every launch. If you receive a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"rate-limiting error while testing your app, stop your app in Xcode and re-launch","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it to reset the rate counter.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/technologies","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel"],["doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/technologies","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/LanguageModelSession","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel"],["doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/technologies","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/Adapter"],["doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/technologies","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/LanguageModelSession","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/Foun